UML = Unified Modeling Language 

It is visual represenration of a system or software

Purpose: 
Understand desgin, code architecture and implementation
Model workflows and business process
Visualize potential outcomes or errors in programs

Types of UML Diagrams 
Class diagram: Represnts and abstract model of classes and their relationship
Object diagram: Represent an instance of class diagram at a particulat moment 
Compontnt diagram: Breaks down a system into smaller components and shows how thry relate 
Deployment diagram: Models the physical depliyment of systems components 
Composite Structure diagram: Shows how a class, component or collaboration is made up of smaller elements
Package diagram: Shows dependencied between packages and their internal composition

